29/04/2004
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- A former UN official and two local officials of the telecommunications company PTK have been arrested by UN police on corruption charges.
According to a UN statement, police on Wednesday (28 April) arrested Uno Nilsson, a former UNMIK employee and former PTK senior adviser;
former PTK director general Leme Xhema;
and former PTK telecom director Bedri Rama.
Financial investigators initiated the arrests after checking procurement deals and the execution of contracts signed for PTK, a public company under local and UN management.
UNMIK chief Harri Holkeri praised the arrests, reiterating the UN's position of "zero tolerance for corruption".
(AFP - 29/04/04)
